- No speaking, right?

1009
01:00:41,800 --> 01:00:44,041
No! On your knees.

1010
01:00:44,134 --> 01:00:46,580
Bend, bow.

1011
01:00:47,267 --> 01:00:51,443
Look, this is the complete
bow. Do this.

1012
01:00:53,267 --> 01:00:54,837
What are you doing?

1013
01:00:54,900 --> 01:00:56,402
This is the standing bow.

1014
01:00:56,467 --> 01:00:57,969
Bow as you stand.

1015
01:00:58,067 --> 01:00:59,478
I am standing on my legs
and I'm bowing.

1016
01:00:59,534 --> 01:01:01,172
A standing bow.

1017
01:01:01,267 --> 01:01:02,974
Why don't you read it?

1018
01:01:04,867 --> 01:01:07,143
When Joseph and his comrades...

1019
01:01:07,400 --> 01:01:09,107
When Joseph and his comrades...

1020
01:01:09,200 --> 01:01:11,043
...left the ship to
embark on the island...

1021
01:01:11,100 --> 01:01:13,307
...the cruel Jalaal stood there
leering...

1022
01:01:13,367 --> 01:01:14,937
...while standing
tied up in chains.

1023
01:01:16,467 --> 01:01:18,140
That's a lot of emphasis.

1024
01:01:18,234 --> 01:01:19,474
Doesn't it hurt your throat?

1025
01:01:20,500 --> 01:01:21,535
A drink!

1026
01:01:21,633 --> 01:01:24,113
Striding along,
lighting up the path...

1027
01:01:24,167 --> 01:01:27,080
Lighting...

1028
01:01:27,134 --> 01:01:28,772
Sir, please pay attention first.
- Yes.

1029
01:01:28,867 --> 01:01:30,107
Striding along, lighting up
the path.

1030
01:01:30,167 --> 01:01:31,475
Striding along...

1031
01:01:31,534 --> 01:01:33,775
Striding along,
lighting up the path.

1032
01:01:33,867 --> 01:01:36,473
Brandishing the trident
and the crescent moon...

1033
01:01:36,533 --> 01:01:38,410
Don't chatter.
Don't talk nonsense.

1034
01:01:38,467 --> 01:01:41,175
Go and wash your face in a
dirty water canal.

1035
01:01:41,233 --> 01:01:43,736
What are you...
I'm going. - Get going!

1036
01:01:43,834 --> 01:01:45,745
Get going!
- I'm leaving. - Dharam!

1037
01:01:45,800 --> 01:01:47,507
I am leaving.

1038
01:01:47,567 --> 01:01:50,741
I will never come back!
He's insane!

1039
01:01:52,767 --> 01:01:54,576
Hello, may I speak
to Dr. Chunnawala?

1040
01:01:54,900 --> 01:01:56,573
Yes, from your
psychiatry department.

1041
01:02:25,833 --> 01:02:28,575
Get back a bit.
Scoot back!

1042
01:02:32,667 --> 01:02:34,772
Sir, please move a bit forward.

1043
01:02:35,367 --> 01:02:36,573
A bit more.

1044
01:02:51,600 --> 01:02:53,011
Here you are.

1045
01:02:55,500 --> 01:02:57,070
Eat it.

1046
01:02:57,167 --> 01:03:00,011
I am being religious for you.
Eat up. - No.

1047
01:03:00,234 --> 01:03:03,113
You promise like a politician and
forget it, later.

1048
01:03:03,167 --> 01:03:05,477
What did I forget? - You haven't
been to the ashram since two days.

1049
01:03:05,567 --> 01:03:07,478
My son, I have to go to the
market early in the morning.

1050
01:03:07,567 --> 01:03:09,706
You can't get fresh produce
after 9 AM.

1051
01:03:09,767 --> 01:03:10,905
No, it's an excuse.

1052
01:03:10,967 --> 01:03:12,378
Come with me to the ashram
today.

1053
01:03:12,467 --> 01:03:13,741
Neeleshwarji will be there.

1054
01:03:13,800 --> 01:03:16,041
At least greet him.
Baba!

1055
01:03:16,134 --> 01:03:19,445
Listen! - He must see
you attend the veneration.

1056
01:03:19,700 --> 01:03:22,112
Higher.
- Wait till the veneration is complete.

1057
01:03:22,167 --> 01:03:24,238
Please?
- That's right!

1058
01:03:24,434 --> 01:03:26,778
That's right.
Keep it right there.

1059
01:03:28,500 --> 01:03:30,446
Hello?
- Assalam alaikum.

1060
01:03:31,000 --> 01:03:33,844
I am calling from the Khwaja Garib
Nawaz sanatorium. - Yes.

1061
01:03:33,934 --> 01:03:36,915
I thought, I should tell you
your dad is unwell.

1062
01:03:37,267 --> 01:03:39,406
What do you mean?
- He's critical"

1063
01:03:39,800 --> 01:03:42,440
You mean, he is really ill.
- Yes, he is.

1064
01:03:42,900 --> 01:03:45,141
Then, I will come there, Ali Bhai.
- No, listen to me.

1065
01:03:45,200 --> 01:03:46,907
Yes?
- Come during prayers.

1066
01:03:46,967 --> 01:03:48,503
He should not find out.

1067
01:03:48,567 --> 01:03:50,046
He won't know.

1068
01:03:50,367 --> 01:03:52,005
What is it?
- What?

1069
01:03:52,500 --> 01:03:54,104
It's a call from the shop.

1070
01:03:54,300 --> 01:03:55,677
So, you're not staying for
the veneration?

1071
01:03:55,767 --> 01:03:57,872
I will attend the
evening veneration, okay?

1072
01:03:57,934 --> 01:03:59,379
Dad, is there any problem?

1073
01:03:59,467 --> 01:04:01,743
It's nothing, it's just
about the business.

1074
01:04:02,033 --> 01:04:03,569
Why don't you go?

1075
01:04:03,667 --> 01:04:06,978
That's right.
Keep it right there.

1076
01:05:04,133 --> 01:05:07,580
Listen, Lord, I am at your abode.

1077
01:05:08,334 --> 01:05:13,079
At least let me meet my dad, now.
Please? Atleast once.

1078
01:05:22,500 --> 01:05:23,979
Salam alaikum.

1079
01:05:27,500 --> 01:05:28,945
Walaikum salam.

1080
01:05:29,034 --> 01:05:30,445
Shame on you!

1081
01:05:30,500 --> 01:05:32,980
How could you be so rude
while praying?

1082
01:05:33,034 --> 01:05:34,707
You lied in the abode of the Lord!

1083
01:05:34,800 --> 01:05:35,972
Get him out of here, right now.

1084
01:05:36,034 --> 01:05:38,480
Listen to me, my dad
doesn't have much time.

1085
01:05:38,567 --> 01:05:40,513
Let me meet him.
- The law is the law.

1086
01:05:40,600 --> 01:05:42,602
A non Muslim can't go in
and that's that.

1087
01:05:42,667 --> 01:05:44,647
Take him away!
- You know I am a Muslim.

1088
01:05:44,700 --> 01:05:46,008
I am a born Muslim.

1089
01:05:46,067 --> 01:05:47,774
Sir, you know it.
Sir...

1090
01:05:48,400 --> 01:05:50,038
lam a Muslim, sir!
- Come on.

1091
01:05:52,800 --> 01:05:54,040
Alright, fine.

1092
01:06:25,867 --> 01:06:28,040
Amit, what are you saying?
- Mom, it's true!

1093
01:06:28,134 --> 01:06:29,613
I saw Dad myself.

1094
01:06:29,667 --> 01:06:32,671
He was standing outside the mosque
amongst the Muslims wearing the cap.

1095
01:06:32,734 --> 01:06:35,271
For the sake of my father
and my son...

1096
01:06:35,367 --> 01:06:37,278
...and the Holy Spirit, Amen.

1097
01:06:37,367 --> 01:06:40,871
Oh, God, forgive them, for they
know not what I do.

1098
01:06:41,734 --> 01:06:43,077
What is going on, Dharam?

1099
01:06:43,134 --> 01:06:45,774
Amit said, you went to the mosque.

1100
01:06:45,834 --> 01:06:47,575
And you were behaving
like a proper Muslim!

1101
01:06:47,667 --> 01:06:50,147
I even went to church.
He didn't see that.

1102
01:06:51,100 --> 01:06:54,104
Jesus never fails.
But, has he passed?

1103
01:06:54,167 --> 01:06:56,204
Dad, why are you doing this?

1104
01:06:56,400 --> 01:06:59,779
For the sake of my father,
my son and the Holy Spirit, dear.

1105
01:06:59,834 --> 01:07:03,839
I would like to ask God, Allah,
the Almighty.

1106
01:07:03,900 --> 01:07:07,143
If you are one,
why are there so many variations?

1107
01:07:07,200 --> 01:07:09,009
Why these different
departments?

1108
01:07:09,400 --> 01:07:10,936
Due to your identification...

1109
01:07:11,000 --> 01:07:13,276
...competition has been
caused in your creation.

1110
01:07:13,367 --> 01:07:15,745
I want solution for this confusion.

1111
01:07:15,800 --> 01:07:18,610
Please! Please, give me a
solution... - Listen!

1112
01:07:18,667 --> 01:07:20,340
...to this confusion!
Please!

1113
01:07:20,400 --> 01:07:23,006
This is an action or an opinion of
an inadequate reason.

1114
01:07:23,067 --> 01:07:24,569
And this is all
because of you, Amit.

1115
01:07:24,667 --> 01:07:26,772
Ever since you forced him to
be religious...

1116
01:07:26,833 --> 01:07:28,210
...dad has become like this.

1117
01:07:28,267 --> 01:07:29,746
I talked to Dr. Chunawala.

1118
01:07:29,800 --> 01:07:32,007
He said, just leave him alone.
It will be alright.

1119
01:07:32,100 --> 01:07:34,205
So, just stop harassing him.

1120
01:07:35,867 --> 01:07:38,108
Hail Lord Shiva.

1121
01:07:38,400 --> 01:07:39,743
Come, sister.

1122
01:07:40,100 --> 01:07:42,512
Your horoscope is excellent.

1123
01:07:42,833 --> 01:07:45,814
But, there is some unrest
at present.

1124
01:07:46,300 --> 01:07:49,372
Saturn has adversely
aspected the seventh house.

1125
01:07:49,434 --> 01:07:52,381
So, you could have problems with
your husband.

1126
01:07:53,100 --> 01:07:55,273
What kind of problems, priest?

1127
01:07:55,600 --> 01:07:57,204
Please explain.

1128
01:07:57,700 --> 01:07:59,805
I mean, is it work, money...
- Sister...

1129
01:07:59,867 --> 01:08:01,710
...there are other spheres
apart from these.

1130
01:08:01,800 --> 01:08:03,279
Such as the sphere
of moral character.

1131
01:08:04,300 --> 01:08:05,745
Character?

1132
01:08:06,267 --> 01:08:08,247
Are you saying,
there's another woman?

1133
01:08:08,300 --> 01:08:09,643
Hail Lord Shiva!

1134
01:08:09,700 --> 01:08:12,237
Another woman?
Or perhaps another...

1135
01:08:13,400 --> 01:08:15,812
The trouble is in the
seventh house.

1136
01:08:15,867 --> 01:08:17,972
The problem is, that
being a man, the first house...

1137
01:08:18,067 --> 01:08:20,069
...he is involved
with a male planet.

1138
01:08:20,134 --> 01:08:22,614
Don't ask me any more
and put me in a moral dilemma.

1139
01:08:23,000 --> 01:08:25,412
In fact, focus on your
husband's...

1140
01:08:25,467 --> 01:08:27,208
...strange behavior.

1141
01:08:28,467 --> 01:08:31,744
Priest, can't anything be done
about this?

1142
01:08:32,267 --> 01:08:33,541
Listen.

1143
01:08:34,834 --> 01:08:37,075
I have stopped solving
such problems, these days.

1144
01:08:37,167 --> 01:08:39,147
Alright, then.
Bless you.

1145
01:09:20,034 --> 01:09:21,377
What are you looking at?

1146
01:09:22,700 --> 01:09:25,647
I am doing something important.
You won't understand.

1147
01:09:25,967 --> 01:09:27,640
I know it very well!

1148
01:09:27,734 --> 01:09:29,839
What's going on with you
and Mehmood.

1149
01:09:29,933 --> 01:09:31,344
I know all about it.

1150
01:09:32,967 --> 01:09:34,378
Who told you?

1151
01:09:34,934 --> 01:09:36,607
What has to be said about that?

1152
01:09:36,667 --> 01:09:38,305
Can't I see it?

1153
01:09:38,400 --> 01:09:42,212
I have watched you scale
the wall to disgrace yourself.

1154
01:09:43,634 --> 01:09:46,478
Indu, I was going
to tell you, but...

1155
01:09:46,934 --> 01:09:48,845
How could I tell you?

1156
01:09:49,767 --> 01:09:51,246
Oh, Goddess!

1157
01:09:52,667 --> 01:09:54,476
Why did this happen to me?

1158
01:09:54,700 --> 01:09:57,010
Why was I fated to deal
with this?

1159
01:09:57,867 --> 01:09:59,244
Go away.

1160
01:09:59,334 --> 01:10:00,779
Leave and go to Mehmood!

1161
01:10:00,834 --> 01:10:03,371
You like him, right?
Just go to him.

1162
01:10:04,234 --> 01:10:07,545
What? I like Mehmood?

1163
01:10:10,234 --> 01:10:11,975
Are you insane?

1164
01:10:12,300 --> 01:10:13,973
What do you mean, I like him?

1165
01:10:14,167 --> 01:10:16,238
I am not gay, you fool!

1166
01:10:16,967 --> 01:10:20,073
I am straight, straight
as an arrow.

1167
01:10:20,567 --> 01:10:22,843
Why do go to meet him
on the sly, then?

1168
01:10:23,267 --> 01:10:24,405
For you.

1169
01:10:24,467 --> 01:10:26,242
To Mehmod's place?
- Yes.

1170
01:10:26,634 --> 01:10:30,207
We are going to celebrate our 25th
wedding anniversary after a week.

1171
01:10:30,934 --> 01:10:34,279
I want to take you on a honeymoon.

1172
01:10:34,367 --> 01:10:37,007
It will be even more awesome
than the first time around.

1173
01:10:38,067 --> 01:10:41,412
Why do you have to visit
Mehmood at home for that?

1174
01:10:42,500 --> 01:10:44,741
I have to!

1175
01:10:44,834 --> 01:10:48,179
He has some Yunani medicines.

1176
01:10:48,234 --> 01:10:50,771
It adds to a man's vitality.
Okay?

1177
01:10:50,934 --> 01:10:53,005
Yes, so, you could go about
it the regular way.

1178
01:10:53,267 --> 01:10:56,111
Why scale the wall?
- I wanted to surprise you!

1179
01:10:56,167 --> 01:10:59,171
To surprise you,
I'd scale his wall...

1180
01:10:59,267 --> 01:11:01,907
...as well as the Great
Wall of China, too!

1181
01:11:02,501 --> 01:11:04,606
Swear to me.
- It's true.

1182
01:11:04,700 --> 01:11:06,543
I want proof.
- Don't believe me?

1183
01:11:06,600 --> 01:11:09,308
Promise me.
- One moment.

1184
01:11:12,567 --> 01:11:16,379
First, use and then believe it.
Come along.

1185
01:11:18,501 --> 01:11:19,878
Don't laugh!

1186
01:11:19,934 --> 01:11:21,914
It was a narrow escape.

1187
01:11:23,234 --> 01:11:24,907
Once the Maulvi agrees...

1188
01:11:24,967 --> 01:11:27,709
...I will meet my dad
and this charade will stop.

1189
01:11:28,800 --> 01:11:32,247
You overruled my idea of
going to court.

1190
01:11:32,300 --> 01:11:35,076
If you hadn't done that,
that wretched clergyman...

1191
01:11:35,134 --> 01:11:36,943
...would have been set right
in no time.

1192
01:11:37,000 --> 01:11:38,536
What do you think?

1193
01:11:38,600 --> 01:11:41,547
Am I ready to meet him?
- Yes.

1194
01:11:42,100 --> 01:11:46,276
Your Muslim customs,
formalities, etiquettes, life...

1195
01:11:46,334 --> 01:11:49,110
...have I imbibed all of that?

1196
01:11:49,167 --> 01:11:51,113
You're alight.
- Okay.

1197
01:11:51,200 --> 01:11:54,010
But, don't pronounce etiquettes
with a slur.

1198
01:11:57,701 --> 01:12:00,113
What is this?
- ...to celebrate the aqiqah...

1199
01:12:00,167 --> 01:12:02,340
Great! He is my client.

1200
01:12:02,434 --> 01:12:04,505
Mr. Akbar Zariwala.

1201
01:12:04,600 --> 01:12:07,080
It is an invite to an aqiqah
(ritual after child's birth).

1202
01:12:07,334 --> 01:12:08,369
Come with me.

1203
01:12:08,467 --> 01:12:11,311
It's experience on the ground
and you will learn from it.

1204
01:12:11,601 --> 01:12:13,137
What's an aqiqah?

1205
01:12:13,234 --> 01:12:15,646
You will know, when you get there.

1206
01:12:16,967 --> 01:12:19,846
Don't get me into trouble.
- No! Aqiqah.

1207
01:12:20,000 --> 01:12:22,071
Aqiqah,
<i>'</i> Aqiqah,

1208
01:12:22,267 --> 01:12:24,611
Aqiqah!
Forget it.

1209
01:12:24,867 --> 01:12:26,608
Salam alaikum.
How are you?

1210
01:12:26,667 --> 01:12:28,510
You've arranged everything
very well. - Yes.

1211
01:12:29,200 --> 01:12:31,077
I believe you've opened
a new shop.

1212
01:12:31,667 --> 01:12:33,305
God has been kind.

1213
01:12:33,467 --> 01:12:35,003
Did you hear about Rafique?

1214
01:12:35,067 --> 01:12:36,944
Where is your aunt?

1215
01:12:37,300 --> 01:12:40,042
Amazing!
- Thank you.

1216
01:12:40,334 --> 01:12:42,109
Assalam alaikum.
- Walaikum salam.

1217
01:12:42,200 --> 01:12:43,474
All well?

1218
01:12:43,534 --> 01:12:45,844
Salam alaikum, Sir.
- Walaikum salam. All well?

1219
01:12:45,900 --> 01:12:46,970
God is kind.
- Alright.

1220
01:12:47,034 --> 01:12:48,877
This is a special friend of mine.

1221
01:12:48,934 --> 01:12:50,072
A very close and dear friend.

1222
01:12:50,167 --> 01:12:52,010
Do take very good care of him.

1223
01:12:52,067 --> 01:12:53,512
Of course.

1224
01:12:53,601 --> 01:12:54,875
This is Ejaz.
- Hello.

1225
01:12:54,934 --> 01:12:56,379
This is Sahir.

1226
01:12:58,134 --> 01:12:59,670
I will be back.
- Hello.

1227
01:12:59,900 --> 01:13:00,776
I'll be right back.

1228
01:13:01,767 --> 01:13:03,940
So, Sir...
- Hello, ma'am.

1229
01:13:04,000 --> 01:13:06,378
Kids these days ask the most
weird questions.

1230
01:13:06,434 --> 01:13:09,005
It is difficult to answer them.
- Yes.

1231
01:13:09,434 --> 01:13:12,904
Just yesterday my son was
saying...

1232
01:13:12,967 --> 01:13:15,675
...that, if you can't perform Wazu...

1233
01:13:15,767 --> 01:13:17,269
...will the prayer be accepted?

1234
01:13:17,367 --> 01:13:19,347
Now tell me, what should I say?

1235
01:13:28,867 --> 01:13:30,972
It hurts to sit like this.

1236
01:13:31,801 --> 01:13:36,079
No, those who find it tough to sit
in this posture...

1237
01:13:36,134 --> 01:13:38,705
...they have another option.
Yes.

1238
01:13:38,767 --> 01:13:41,270
They can sit on a chair
and perform their prayers.

1239
01:13:41,367 --> 01:13:43,574
The intention has to be pure.
- Right.

1240
01:13:44,767 --> 01:13:48,943
You can perform prayers
while sitting in a chair.

1241
01:13:49,534 --> 01:13:51,138
What?
- Yes.

1242
01:13:51,201 --> 01:13:53,181
Make sure your intentions
are good.

1243
01:13:53,234 --> 01:13:55,407
If you are good, then
anything is good for you.

1244
01:13:55,600 --> 01:13:58,206
Wonderful!
- Well said.

1245
01:13:58,300 --> 01:13:59,973
Amazing.
- You bet.

1246
01:14:01,534 --> 01:14:04,572
I don't know you.
lam Shahzeb Khan.

1247
01:14:04,667 --> 01:14:06,510
What's your good name?

1248
01:14:07,100 --> 01:14:08,738
Sharif Khan.

1249
01:14:09,801 --> 01:14:12,543
You seem to be wise and
learned man.

1250
01:14:12,634 --> 01:14:15,513
Tell me, is it a sin to
grow one's hair?

1251
01:14:22,000 --> 01:14:23,104
Mom!

1252
01:14:24,701 --> 01:14:26,942
